data.description: Welcome to this beautiful move-in ready Palm Harbor home on a rare and spacious corner lot within The Hamptons at Lake St George South community. 1,661 living square feet includes 2 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, a den/office area that has double doors for privacy, plus a converted garage which is effectively a 4th room/bonus room that is not included in the heated square footage! Converted garage could be easily turned back into a useable garage. The location is hard to beat in a peaceful neighborhood where you have access to excellent schools including Lake St George Elementary and Palm Harbor Middle. The delightful screened-in front porch offers privacy and a relaxing area, with a handy storage closet adjacent to it just outside of the front door. While inside the house, the open-concept family room with vaulted ceilings, large windows, and dining area makes you feel immediately at home. Its charming kitchen may be compact but it's bursting with character and efficiency. Perfectly suited for those who appreciate simplicity without sacrificing functionality, this kitchen is a testament to smart design and thoughtful organization. Modern stainless steel appliances are included. Make chores a breeze by having your washer and dryer neatly tucked away in the laundry closet adjacent to your kitchen for maximum convenience. Step through the rear sliding glass doors into the epitome of home entertainment with this luxurious enclosed space, equipped with a full bar, classy brick fireplace and ceiling fans, that effortlessly combines relaxation, sports excitement, and unforgettable parties! Nestled within your home, this entertainment/bar area is ideal for those who crave the perfect setting to host gatherings and unwind after a day of work. Walk out through your side patio door which leads you to a large private yard with a newly paved outdoor area, enclosed by two sides of 6-foot fencing and one side of 4-foot fencing, but don't let that short fence fool you because this home's yard continues past the short fence around to the back of the house!! The sellers did not use that precious backyard area, so make sure to take advantage of your ENTIRE yard! Please reference the aerial drone photos to see the boundary lines. The storage shed in the backyard stays. Rest easy as the big ticket items are well within their useful age: the A/C unit is from 2021, roof is from 2014, and water heater is from 2015. The HOA fee is very low at $210/YEAR and NO flood zone.
